1
00:01:18,145 --> 00:01:19,711
<i>Don't listen to
the haters, norm.</i>

2
00:01:19,713 --> 00:01:22,114
<i>You're a polar bear.
You got this.</i>

3
00:01:22,116 --> 00:01:23,749
<i>I mean, look at those paws.</i>

4
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:26,452
<i>You're an animal...
Literally.</i>

5
00:01:26,454 --> 00:01:29,421
<i>It's all-you-can-eat
seal buffet.</i>

6
00:01:29,423 --> 00:01:30,856
<i>Go fill your plate.</i>

7
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:38,363
Read 'em and weep, boys.

8
00:01:38,365 --> 00:01:41,200
Cari-boo-yah!
Full house.

9
00:01:43,337 --> 00:01:45,337
I'd bet antlers he fails again.

10
00:01:45,339 --> 00:01:47,272
Ah, he looks hungry.

11
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:49,374
I'm giving ten-to-one odds
he catches the poor Pinniped.

12
00:01:49,376 --> 00:01:51,276
They say I can't hunt.

13
00:01:53,714 --> 00:01:55,214
Huh?

14
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:09,761
Oy, phooey! How can I be
king if I can't hunt?

15
00:02:10,898 --> 00:02:12,464
Ooh-ooh!

16
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:13,632
Uh-uh-uh!

17
00:02:28,749 --> 00:02:30,716
This is gonna hurt.

18
00:02:30,718 --> 00:02:31,917
Oh!

19
00:02:33,521 --> 00:02:35,154
That wasn't so bad.

20
00:02:35,156 --> 00:02:38,157
- Oy, that was bad.

21
00:02:40,394 --> 00:02:41,760
They say he doesn't
have any focus.

22
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:44,863
Huh?
Hi, Elizabeth.

23
00:02:44,865 --> 00:02:46,865
Hi.

24
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:49,801
Ugh!

25
00:02:49,803 --> 00:02:52,804
Jeez, it's like
pure ice up here.

26
00:02:52,806 --> 00:02:54,740
An accident waiting
to happen, you know?

27
00:02:54,742 --> 00:02:56,642
I mean, somebody should really
do something about this, huh?

28
00:02:56,644 --> 00:02:58,177
Ahem.
Lemmings.

29
00:03:08,522 --> 00:03:10,289
Anyway, I really
should get goin' now.

30
00:03:10,291 --> 00:03:12,791
I've got a seal to go
catch and eat and I...

31
00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:16,495
Anyway, I uh...
See ya, gotta go.

32
00:03:16,497 --> 00:03:19,198
Bye now. Catch ya
later, Elizabeth.

33
00:03:28,409 --> 00:03:30,442
Babe, look!
A hunt!

34
00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:32,411
This trip is finally payin' off.

35
00:03:38,986 --> 00:03:40,886
Any last words before I eat you?

36
00:03:45,793 --> 00:03:48,794
Oh, come on.
Don't say that.

37
00:03:48,796 --> 00:03:51,630
You always know exactly
what to say to get to me.

38
00:03:51,632 --> 00:03:53,665
Eat him. Eat him!

39
00:03:53,667 --> 00:03:55,400
- Yeah! Eat him.
- Eat him!

40
00:03:56,937 --> 00:03:58,870
You wanna know why I'm
not gonna eat you?

41
00:03:58,872 --> 00:04:01,940
You got a minute?
Well, maybe an hour.

42
00:04:01,942 --> 00:04:05,711
It all started when I turned 13.

43
00:04:05,713 --> 00:04:08,380
<i>In health class they told us
how our growl would change,</i>

44
00:04:08,382 --> 00:04:10,649
<i>how we'd start getting
more fur on our bodies.</i>

45
00:04:10,651 --> 00:04:14,019
<i>But they didn't say anything
about speaking to humans.</i>

46
00:04:15,856 --> 00:04:18,890
I want one! I want one!
I want one! I want one!

47
00:04:20,728 --> 00:04:23,328
Aren't they supposed to stay
50 yards away?

48
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:27,266
If this little brat takes one
more step, I'm gonna pounce.

49
00:04:28,636 --> 00:04:30,569
Keep it up, kid.

50
00:04:30,571 --> 00:04:32,838
The only thing you're
gonna get is a mauling.

51
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:35,874
Can't ya see we're
wild animals here?

52
00:04:35,876 --> 00:04:38,677
Did you just talk to me?

53
00:04:38,679 --> 00:04:40,879
Wait.
You can speak bear?

54
00:04:40,881 --> 00:04:44,750
No, dummy, you're
speaking human.

55
00:04:48,555 --> 00:04:50,756
I didn't know what to do.

56
00:04:50,758 --> 00:04:54,026
No other bear seemed to
be able to speak human.

57
00:04:54,028 --> 00:04:57,996
And certainly no other bear had
these weird feelings that I had.

58
00:04:57,998 --> 00:05:01,033
So I went to go see the
wisest bear in the world.

59
00:05:01,035 --> 00:05:02,968
The king of the arctic,

60
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:05,370
who conveniently
was also my grandpa.

61
00:05:09,710 --> 00:05:12,577
- I don't know what to do.
- I didn't ask for this.

62
00:05:12,579 --> 00:05:14,513
What is wrong with me?

63
00:05:14,515 --> 00:05:17,549
Nothing is wrong with you, norm.
You're special.

64
00:05:17,551 --> 00:05:20,018
Yeah, a real one of a kind.

65
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:22,888
Actually, more like
two of a kind.

66
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,723
I share the same trait.

67
00:05:24,725 --> 00:05:27,626
I, too, can speak
to our human visitors.

68
00:05:27,628 --> 00:05:29,861
You can talk to them, too?

69
00:05:29,863 --> 00:05:31,697
I can.

70
00:05:31,699 --> 00:05:34,466
Polar bears are icons
of the arctic, norm.

71
00:05:34,468 --> 00:05:38,637
And an icon with a voice
can be very powerful indeed.

72
00:05:38,639 --> 00:05:40,739
Our land is vulnerable

73
00:05:40,741 --> 00:05:43,809
and we're responsible.

74
00:05:43,811 --> 00:05:48,113
For now, just know
that what you and I have

75
00:05:48,115 --> 00:05:49,948
is a great gift.

76
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:54,086
One day you'll truly understand.

77
00:05:54,088 --> 00:05:56,488
But when will I understand?

78
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:57,956
<i>But if didn't end there.</i>

79
00:05:57,958 --> 00:06:01,059
<i>Human tendencies
had taken over my body.</i>

80
00:06:03,063 --> 00:06:05,964
<i>That's when I started doing
the arctic shake.</i>

81
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:14,005
<i>I put the "soul"
in winter solstice.</i>

82
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:26,718
These days, I'm pretty glad
I have these feelings,

83
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,587
but I just don't know
what to do with them.

84
00:06:28,589 --> 00:06:30,021
And that brings me
to the other day.

85
00:06:38,932 --> 00:06:42,868
Why don't you take a picture?
It'll last longer.

86
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:44,970
I knew he wouldn't
kill the seal.

87
00:06:44,972 --> 00:06:47,739
- Pay up.
- Fine, here.

88
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:50,409
You're lucky these
things grow back.

89
00:07:01,488 --> 00:07:05,190
I'm a bear who can't hunt.
I'm soft and frozen yogurt.

90
00:07:05,192 --> 00:07:07,626
Who needs a bear
with too much care

91
00:07:07,628 --> 00:07:09,027
and not enough scare?

92
00:07:09,029 --> 00:07:11,830
Norm! What is that, a haiku?

93
00:07:11,832 --> 00:07:14,499
What did dad tell you
about writing poetry?

94
00:07:14,501 --> 00:07:17,836
I know, I know. "Leave the
poetry to the panda bears."

95
00:07:17,838 --> 00:07:19,571
What's up, Sam?

96
00:07:19,573 --> 00:07:21,540
I only caught
the tail end of it...

97
00:07:21,542 --> 00:07:24,142
But I made some money off your
failed hunt today, big bro.

98
00:07:25,913 --> 00:07:28,113
I wish I'd caught
the tail end of my hunt.

99
00:07:28,115 --> 00:07:29,681
Let me give you
some advice, bro.

100
00:07:29,683 --> 00:07:31,783
Act with your stomach
and not your heart.

101
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:33,452
- - Huh?

102
00:07:38,892 --> 00:07:41,460
Oh, my 5:00 is here.
Excuse me, Normie.

103
00:07:41,462 --> 00:07:43,628
I don't know why you spend
so much time and energy

104
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:46,465
on these tourists.
They're ruining it up here.

105
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:48,900
<i>Au contraire, Mon frère.</i>

106
00:07:48,902 --> 00:07:51,837
As dad always said, "if humans
come to our land and clap,

107
00:07:51,839 --> 00:07:53,939
they can't come
to our land and crap."

108
00:07:53,941 --> 00:07:55,907
"Give them a scene..."

109
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:57,943
"The arctic
stays clean."

110
00:07:57,945 --> 00:08:00,612
Thanks, Stan, I got it.
But grandpa always said...

111
00:08:00,614 --> 00:08:03,915
Enough about grandpa, norm.
He left us, remember?

112
00:08:03,917 --> 00:08:06,017
He's not here.
We are.

113
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:09,221
The humans won't destroy
something they love.

114
00:08:09,223 --> 00:08:10,856
And they love...

115
00:08:10,858 --> 00:08:13,792
Us.

116
00:08:13,794 --> 00:08:17,128
Let's give these people what they
came a thousand miles to see.

117
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:18,563
A show!

118
00:08:18,565 --> 00:08:21,132
And go!

119
00:08:39,152 --> 00:08:40,785
Whoa!

120
00:08:46,126 --> 00:08:47,792
You ain't seen nothin' yet.

121
00:08:47,794 --> 00:08:50,028
Whales, I need whales.

122
00:09:00,741 --> 00:09:04,276
How many times do I have to tell you?
This ain't Orlando.

123
00:09:04,278 --> 00:09:05,777
Act real.

124
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:15,320
Oh, not that real.

125
00:09:15,322 --> 00:09:17,322
Oh, that's the fourth
time this month.

126
00:09:17,324 --> 00:09:19,758
Norm, I need you for the finale.

127
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:22,127
I'm desperate. A whale
just ate my actor.

128
00:09:22,129 --> 00:09:24,029
This is my nightmare.

129
00:09:24,031 --> 00:09:26,698
Oh, please.

130
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:29,601
No, the arctic shake was
for your bachelor party.

131
00:09:29,603 --> 00:09:31,803
I'd never do that
for the human tourists.

132
00:09:31,805 --> 00:09:33,672
Never, never, never.

133
00:10:03,737 --> 00:10:07,105
He doesn't belong in the arctic,
he belongs on Broadway.

134
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:09,374
<i>Right?</i>

135
00:10:14,181 --> 00:10:16,281
<i>Can you do the Charleston?</i>

136
00:10:31,064 --> 00:10:33,898
Socrates!
Oh, wisest of the winged.

137
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,967
Brainiest of the beaked.

138
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:39,738
Norm, grab a seat.

139
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:41,906
Be with you in a minute.
Just finishing up.

140
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:45,710
And the next thing
you know, I'm twerking

141
00:10:45,712 --> 00:10:47,812
in front of a boatload
of human tourists.

142
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:50,749
Twerking! Have some
self-respect, norm.

143
00:10:50,751 --> 00:10:52,150
I just don't know why
everyone wants to be

144
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:54,052
so nice to these intruders.

145
00:10:54,054 --> 00:10:55,687
They've never done
anything for us

146
00:10:55,689 --> 00:10:58,256
except to come to
our land uninvited.

147
00:10:58,258 --> 00:11:00,892
Ah, your grandfather
had a saying...

148
00:11:00,894 --> 00:11:04,696
<i>"Panem et circenses."</i>
"Bread and circuses."

149
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:06,798
He meant it's easier
to distract ourselves

150
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,233
with food and entertainment,

151
00:11:08,235 --> 00:11:10,835
than think about
the real problems.

152
00:11:10,837 --> 00:11:12,771
What happened
to grandpa, Socrates?

153
00:11:12,773 --> 00:11:14,439
Did he really just disappear?

154
00:11:14,441 --> 00:11:15,907
The theories are plentiful.

155
00:11:15,909 --> 00:11:18,209
Some believe he is on
a vision quest.

156
00:11:18,211 --> 00:11:20,845
Some people think he simply
went to search for fish.

157
00:11:20,847 --> 00:11:23,281
While others think he went
to follow the band...

158
00:11:23,283 --> 00:11:25,216
Phish.

159
00:11:25,218 --> 00:11:29,020
Me, I think your grandpa knew
something was happening,

160
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:30,455
and tried to fight it.

161
00:11:30,457 --> 00:11:33,258
And it looks like that
something<i> is</i> happening.

162
00:11:47,474 --> 00:11:50,842
Holy icicle.
Is that a human house?

163
00:11:50,844 --> 00:11:53,178
It's a model home.

164
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:56,181
A sales tool.

165
00:11:56,183 --> 00:11:59,851
Just arrived, literally,
fresh on the boat.

166
00:11:59,853 --> 00:12:02,353
It means more of these
houses are gonna be coming.

167
00:12:02,355 --> 00:12:05,757
Humans are moving here?
To live?

168
00:12:05,759 --> 00:12:07,759
It starts with the tourists,

169
00:12:07,761 --> 00:12:10,261
then someone says,
"I could do this year round."

170
00:12:10,263 --> 00:12:12,831
It happened to my buddy,
Freddy the flamingo.

171
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:14,499
He was in Florida, minding
his own business.

172
00:12:14,501 --> 00:12:16,434
A couple of tourists show up.

173
00:12:16,436 --> 00:12:19,738
Next thing you know, there are
plastic statues of Freddy

174
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:20,872
on everyone's lawn!

175
00:12:30,317 --> 00:12:32,517
We gotta talk to the king.

176
00:12:35,021 --> 00:12:37,455
<i>Norm, that house
has nothing to do</i>

177
00:12:37,457 --> 00:12:39,891
with why grandpa vanished.

178
00:12:41,895 --> 00:12:44,796
Dad, you're not listening,
there's more.

179
00:12:44,798 --> 00:12:47,799
There's a human house
right here on grandpa's land.

180
00:12:47,801 --> 00:12:49,768
<i>Humans are moving here now.</i>

181
00:12:53,507 --> 00:12:56,007
Ah, norm, you always did have

182
00:12:56,009 --> 00:12:57,942
such an imagination,
now, didn't you?

183
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:01,045
- First with the poetry...
- I swear it's true.

184
00:13:01,047 --> 00:13:04,349
Socrates and I snuck in.
And look...

185
00:13:04,351 --> 00:13:06,317
From Florida.

186
00:13:17,197 --> 00:13:19,164
Norm, you are not to go
anywhere near there.

187
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:20,965
Do you hear me?

188
00:13:20,967 --> 00:13:24,068
Grandpa's land is off limits.
Understood?

189
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:26,137
"Snuck in."

190
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:28,973
Norm, you shouldn't
go onto property

191
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:31,476
that doesn't belong to you.
You should know better.

192
00:13:31,478 --> 00:13:33,945
Besides, I'm sure the
house you're referring to

193
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:36,881
is simply a research hut.

194
00:13:36,883 --> 00:13:38,550
<i>Look, son, you wanna be king?</i>

195
00:13:38,552 --> 00:13:41,886
A future king isn't supposed
to get so emotional.

196
00:13:41,888 --> 00:13:44,155
We hunt, we lead, and we sleep.
Simple!

197
00:13:44,157 --> 00:13:46,257
Now there is plenty
of ice to go around.

198
00:13:46,259 --> 00:13:48,860
Just stay away from<i> there!</i>
Far away.

199
00:13:48,862 --> 00:13:51,830
And for the love of salmon,
no more talking human!

200
00:13:51,832 --> 00:13:55,099
- You got me?
- Yes, dad.

201
00:14:12,052 --> 00:14:14,419
Did you see that? He wants
to give away the arctic.

202
00:14:14,421 --> 00:14:15,987
That's it.
We're done.

203
00:14:15,989 --> 00:14:18,590
Norm, it all points
to the same thing.

204
00:14:18,592 --> 00:14:20,625
Humans are invading our land.

205
00:14:20,627 --> 00:14:23,328
And you are a polar bear
who can speak to humans.

206
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:26,197
You're the only one who can
do something about this.

207
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:28,900
Socrates, I can't even hunt.

208
00:14:31,171 --> 00:14:34,105
Norm, your grandpa once told me,

209
00:14:34,107 --> 00:14:36,374
"norm's the only bear
that has the potential

210
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:39,911
to be king of the arctic.

211
00:14:39,913 --> 00:14:42,947
<i>He feels the arctic's pain.</i>

212
00:14:42,949 --> 00:14:45,016
And if he feels it enough,

213
00:14:45,018 --> 00:14:47,585
he'll stand
for us."

214
00:14:50,657 --> 00:14:52,891
I can't even stand for myself.

215
00:14:52,893 --> 00:14:54,926
<i>Norm, don't listen to them.</i>

216
00:14:54,928 --> 00:14:57,295
They're just furry robots
sitting in their ice cubicles

217
00:14:57,297 --> 00:14:59,030
obeying the rules,

218
00:14:59,032 --> 00:15:01,900
pretending nothing bad's
ever gonna happen.

219
00:15:01,902 --> 00:15:04,469
But<i> you</i> can change the rules.

220
00:15:04,471 --> 00:15:07,906
You're seeing the future. They're
just living in the past.

221
00:15:07,908 --> 00:15:10,241
You can find a new way.

222
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:12,243
Don't just dance for the humans.

223
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:14,345
Fight for our home instead.

224
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:20,985
Okay.
I won't let you down.

225
00:15:28,528 --> 00:15:31,629
- Socrates!
- - Cranberries!

226
00:15:31,631 --> 00:15:34,332
Surprise is the
number-one cause of death

227
00:15:34,334 --> 00:15:36,100
in the elderly, you know.

228
00:15:37,504 --> 00:15:39,037
We have to do something.

229
00:15:39,039 --> 00:15:41,105
I have to do something.

230
00:15:41,107 --> 00:15:43,441
Ah, number one or number two?

231
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:46,277
- We gotta take some...
- Man:<i> Action!</i>

232
00:15:52,719 --> 00:15:55,253
<i>What the heck is that?</i> - Caw.

233
00:15:55,255 --> 00:15:57,522
That is proof of why you
should stay in school.

234
00:15:57,524 --> 00:16:00,425
First you're cutting class, next
you're dressing up in a bear suit

235
00:16:00,427 --> 00:16:02,393
<i>doing twirls
for a real estate commercial.</i>

236
00:16:02,395 --> 00:16:04,662
The seals would kill<i> him.</i> Cut!

237
00:16:05,699 --> 00:16:07,231
Who said that?

238
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:08,666
I'm the only one
who yells, "cut!"

239
00:16:08,668 --> 00:16:10,735
I'm the director.

240
00:16:12,706 --> 00:16:15,173
I'm not just going to be
a furry robot

241
00:16:15,175 --> 00:16:17,041
sitting in an ice cubicle.

242
00:16:17,043 --> 00:16:19,010
We have to point that
director in a new direction.

243
00:16:25,418 --> 00:16:28,086
Oh, great. A suit
coming to give me

244
00:16:28,088 --> 00:16:30,588
creative notes
on my masterpiece!

245
00:16:50,443 --> 00:16:51,642
Hmm.

246
00:16:57,050 --> 00:16:59,183
But I'll need soldiers
on the ground.

247
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:03,121
